d 'KSTEST': module to perform weighted two-sample Kolmogorov-Smirnov equality-of-distributions test 
d
d  kstest performs a (optionally weighted) two-sample
d Kolmogorov-Smirnov (KS) permutation test to assess whether two
d samples come from the same distribution.  The KS statistic is the
d single largest absolute difference between the two empirical
d cumulative distribution functions (ECDFs), making it most
d sensitive to a discrepancy that is large and concentrated at one
d location, and less sensitive to differences spread across the
d distribution or concentrated in the tails (see adtest and cvmtest
d for alternative tests better suited to those cases). The
d permutation test provides a valid p-value by comparing the
d observed statistic to its distribution under random reassignment
d of group labels. 
d
d KW: equality of distributions
d KW: two-sample
d KW: Kolmogorov-Smirnov
d KW: comparisons
d KW: weighting
d
d Requires: Stata version 11
d
d Distribution-Date: 20260717
d
d Author: Ariel Linden, Linden Consulting Group, LLC
d Support: email alinden@@lindenconsulting.org
d
